1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Oh, you must be born again is what Jesus said to the religious leader Nicodemus.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
And I'm thankful for that day that I trusted the Lord Jesus Christ as my Savior here in the gospel.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
And that's quite interesting.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:17,000
We sang our great Savior and then we heard I got saved.

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:22,000
And this morning we're going to look at Acts chapter number eight, a familiar passage of Scripture.

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:28,000
But in Acts chapter number eight, we're reminded of a particular Bible character.

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:34,000
The Ethiopian eunuch. We'll be looking at several things from his life this morning in the text of Scripture.

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:40,000
But how he came to know the Lord Jesus Christ as his personal Savior as well.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
And so I am thankful for the opportunity to look at this portion of Scripture this morning.

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
And if you would begin reading with me in verse number 26.

11
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
The Bible says this in Acts 8 and verse 26.

12
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:56,000
And the angel of the Lord spake unto Philip, saying, Arise and go toward the south,

13
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,000
and to the way that goeth down from Jerusalem unto Gaza, which is desert.

14
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Now skip down and read verse 35 with me.

15
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:11,000
The Bible says, Then Philip opened his mouth, began at the same Scripture, and preached unto him Jesus.

16
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:15,000
I'm going to preach a message this morning that I've simply entitled from verse number 35.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Preached unto him Jesus.

18
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
We'll look at the entire text as we get through it this morning.

19
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:26,000
But I want to remind you that Acts chapter number eight is a transitional chapter here in the book of Acts.

20
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,000
We find that in Acts chapter number seven, God records for us the first martyr of the church.

21
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Stephen is stoned. We read that. We understand that.

22
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,000
There was a man that was consenting unto his death. His name was Saul.

23
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:44,000
The Bible tells us as we begin chapter number eight, the persecution against the church intensified.

24
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
It reached a high point level.

25
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:50,000
The pressure and the persecution is coming against the church.

26
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:57,000
And this chapter, Acts chapter number eight, is transitional, but it's also packed with a number of exciting events.

27
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Now remember, the Bible is God's word.

28
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Everything that's contained in the Bible is true.

29
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Every word of God is pure.

30
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:14,000
And the accounts I often refer to as accounts, because they are actual accounts of things that happened.

31
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,000
I don't take offense or want to argue with people that say that they're Bible stories,

32
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:23,000
but I personally like using the phraseology that they're accounts,

33
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:29,000
because sometimes a story can communicate to someone that it's just something that someone made up.

34
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:35,000
In fact, yesterday, as we were out door knocking, someone said to Brother Mark, as we knocked on their door,

35
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
as he said to them something about the importance of God's word and following the Bible,

36
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:44,000
he said, oh, it's just a book of stories written by men.

37
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,000
That's what he said.

38
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:53,000
And it reminded me when I heard him say that, the importance of understanding that every word of God is pure.

39
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:58,000
The events recorded in Acts chapter number eight are actual events that took place,

40
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:04,000
and God is providing us as his people with a record of these events.

41
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
The record is to encourage us.

42
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
The record is to challenge us.

43
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:17,000
The record is to instruct us so that we'd understand some things that happened as God was moving and working through his church.

44
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:24,000
We find that this persecution intensifies, and it comes to the point where the believers are scattered.

45
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:29,000
It's interesting to see that in verse number one, the Bible says that great persecution came,

46
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:34,000
and they were scattered throughout the regions except the apostles.

47
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:40,000
That reveals to us that the apostles stayed there in Jerusalem, but everyone else, they were scattered abroad.

48
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:48,000
And the Bible tells us in verse number four, therefore, they that were scattered abroad went everywhere preaching the word.

49
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,000
And God's word is going forth.

50
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:54,000
The great commission is being fulfilled as we begin reading in Acts chapter number eight,

51
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:59,000
because Jesus said that you're to be witnesses unto me after that the Holy Ghost has come upon you.

52
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:03,000
You're to be witnesses unto me both in Jerusalem, Judea, Samaria, and the uttermost.

53
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:09,000
But they were in Jerusalem, and God used this persecution, something that was meant for evil,

54
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:15,000
something that was meant to cause the people of God to keep their mouth shut, to stop talking about Jesus,

55
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:21,000
and he used it to literally spread the gospel around the world.

56
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,000
And this is the start of it.

57
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
They went everywhere preaching the word.

58
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
We find that Philip is in Samaria.

59
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:34,000
And it's interesting, as Philip is in Samaria, the Bible tells us that there's really a great revival in that city.

60
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,000
I mean, it's amazing what's happening.

61
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:42,000
And the Bible says in verse six, and the people with one accord gave heed unto those things which Philip spake,

62
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,000
hearing and seeing the miracles which he did.

63
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:50,000
And notice in verse number eight, there was great joy in that city.

64
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Why was there joy in the city?

65
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:58,000
They got saved because they understood the truth of who Jesus is and what he did for them.

66
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
And they got saved.

67
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Salvation came to this city of Samaria.

68
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:07,000
There are many that trust at Christ, and there's a great revival that's taking place.

69
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:11,000
In the midst of all of this, God calls Philip.

70
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:15,000
And he calls Philip to leave.

71
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,000
But there's a lot happening in Samaria.

72
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,000
It's exciting what's going on in Samaria.

73
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,000
People are getting saved, and it's exciting.

74
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:30,000
But God calls Philip, and he calls him to leave Samaria to go to a certain place for a specific task.

75
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:37,000
And by way of introduction, I just want to mention, I'm so thankful that as we read the passage of Scripture,

76
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:42,000
that Philip was first sensitive to the voice of God.

77
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,000
He was sensitive to the voice of God.

78
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:50,000
The angel of the Lord, according to verse number 26, spake unto Philip, and he was sensitive.

79
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Do you hear the voice of God?

80
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
Are you listening when you open the word of God?

81
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Are you praying that God would speak to you, that God would teach you?

82
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:03,000
As you enter into church, are you praying and asking God, Lord, speak to me?

83
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,000
Lord, give me truth.

84
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,000
I want to be sensitive.

85
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:11,000
I want to have ears to hear what the Spirit saith.

86
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:19,000
We find that Philip was not only sensitive to the voice of God, but Philip was obedient to the leadership of God.

87
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Philip arose and went just as he had been commanded to do so.

88
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:31,000
And it's interesting as we study throughout the Bible how often you find that God's people obey God's voice.

89
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:36,000
I was reading recently and looking at the life of Moses, and you study through the life of Moses,

90
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:40,000
it's amazing how often God speaks to Moses and he obeys.

91
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,000
He carries out.

92
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:45,000
We understand the disobedience when he was supposed to speak to the rock and he hit it twice.

93
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,000
We understand that.

94
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:55,000
But if you look at the whole of his life, far more often Moses heard the voice of God and obeyed the voice of God.

95
00:06:55,000 --> 00:07:00,000
And oh, that we as the people of God today, we would still hear the voice of God.

96
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,000
How does God speak to us?

97
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Well, he uses his word.

98
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,000
I'm so thankful for the preservation of Scripture.

99
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
I'm thankful for the inspiration of Scripture.

100
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Yes, all Scripture is given by inspiration of God, but we understand that God has preserved his word

101
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:17,000
and God speaks to us through the Bible.

102
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,000
We come to church.

103
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
We hear God's word preached and proclaimed.

104
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:26,000
We hear it taught in Sunday school, and we have the opportunity to hear the instruction.

105
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:30,000
And God has a message for us as individuals.

106
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:36,000
And I'm so thankful that our God who loves the entire world cares about the single person.

107
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,000
He cares about the individual.

108
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,000
He cares about me.

109
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,000
He cares about you.

110
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:47,000
And we see that revealed to us in the text of Scripture because what happens is when Philip leaves Samaria

111
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:51,000
and the revival that's taking place and those that have gotten saved,

112
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:55,000
he tells Philip in verse 25 or 26, excuse me,

113
00:07:56,000 --> 00:08:01,000
unto the way that goeth down from Jerusalem unto Gaza, which is desert.

114
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:10,000
And he arose and went, and behold, a man of Ethiopia, a man of Ethiopia,

115
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:14,000
and eunuch of great authority under Candace, queen of the Ethiopians,

116
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:19,000
who had the charge of all her treasure and had come to Jerusalem for to worship.

117
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:23,000
As we dig into the text this morning, let me share with you number one.

118
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:27,000
If you're taking notes, the confusion of the eunuch.

119
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
The confusion of the eunuch.

120
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:34,000
The Bible tells us in verse 27 that as Philip obeys the voice of the Lord, he arose and went,

121
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:37,000
that he finds this man, a man of Ethiopia.

122
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:41,000
We often refer to him as the Ethiopian eunuch.

123
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:46,000
We find that as we begin digging in to the Scriptures, that as we look at this man,

124
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:52,000
he's returning, he's sitting in his chariot, and he's reading Isaiah the prophet.

125
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,000
He's reading the word of God.

126
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:58,000
He had gone to Jerusalem, we'd see in verse 27, for the purpose of worship.

127
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:01,000
We find in verse 29 that the Spirit said unto Philip,

128
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:05,000
go near and join thyself to this chariot.

129
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:09,000
And Philip ran thither to him and heard him read the prophet Isaiah,

130
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
and said, notice what Philip says to the eunuch,

131
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:16,000
understandest thou what thou readest.

132
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:21,000
We find the confusion of the eunuch beginning to be revealed to us in verse 30 through 34

133
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:25,000
as we begin to see this interaction that Philip has with the eunuch.

134
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:30,000
And we find that this confusion, it's revealed to us that he's confused.

135
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:36,000
He says this when he's asked the question, understandest thou what thou readest.

136
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:40,000
Notice he says in verse 31, how can I?

137
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:45,000
Except some man should guide me.

138
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,000
As we look at the text of Scripture and we consider the confusion of the eunuch,

139
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,000
I want you to see first of all that this man was searching.

140
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,000
He was searching.

141
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,000
You know, there are people today that are searching for answers.

142
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,000
There are people today that are searching for purpose.

143
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
They're searching for understanding.

144
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,180
understanding of why am I here, what is the point,

145
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:06,539
why am I on earth, what is the point of my life,

146
00:10:06,539 --> 00:10:07,880
what is this all about?

147
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,239
There are people that are searching and oftentimes

148
00:10:10,239 --> 00:10:11,840
what happens is people are searching

149
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:13,420
in all the wrong places.

150
00:10:14,359 --> 00:10:19,180
This man was searching and he goes to Jerusalem

151
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:22,440
and he's there, we find the Bible says in verse 27

152
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,840
that he was there in Jerusalem for what purpose?

153
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,680
To worship, he's searching.

154
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:30,079
Do you know that yes, there are some that would say

155
00:10:30,079 --> 00:10:32,520
that they're atheists but I believe if you really press

156
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:35,700
on them real hard, most people acknowledge

157
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:38,520
that there's some higher power.

158
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,840
They acknowledge, listen, the Bible tells us

159
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:43,759
the heavens declare the glory of our God.

160
00:10:43,759 --> 00:10:47,639
We find that as you begin to look at this world

161
00:10:47,639 --> 00:10:50,200
and you begin to analyze, you understand

162
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,720
that there is a creator.

163
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:54,240
I understand Darwinian evolution, I understand

164
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:57,040
the prominence in our society and all of those things

165
00:10:57,439 --> 00:10:59,680
but deep down when you really speak to someone,

166
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:02,720
God has placed it in the heart of every person,

167
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,080
the truth that God is.

168
00:11:06,559 --> 00:11:09,239
This man's in Jerusalem and he's searching.

169
00:11:10,319 --> 00:11:12,419
Can I tell you, he went to the right place

170
00:11:13,599 --> 00:11:14,879
but he leaves empty.

171
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:19,519
He left Jerusalem and while he was there in Jerusalem,

172
00:11:19,519 --> 00:11:21,599
there was no one that gave him an answer.

173
00:11:21,599 --> 00:11:24,239
There's a lot going on in Jerusalem at this time

174
00:11:24,239 --> 00:11:27,040
but he leaves Jerusalem and as he's leaving,

175
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:29,879
he's reading Isaiah the prophet.

176
00:11:29,879 --> 00:11:33,279
Not only did he go to Jerusalem but now he's sitting

177
00:11:33,279 --> 00:11:36,279
and he's actually reading the scriptures

178
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:39,599
and as he's reading the scriptures, we find that God,

179
00:11:39,599 --> 00:11:42,879
knowing all things and loving all men,

180
00:11:42,879 --> 00:11:45,120
we find that the Bible tells us that he's not willing

181
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,180
that any should perish but that all should come

182
00:11:47,180 --> 00:11:49,519
to repentance and he sees this one

183
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:53,160
and he knows his position and he knows the faithfulness

184
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:55,559
of Philip and he calls Philip to go

185
00:11:56,959 --> 00:12:01,959
and Philip says, understand this now what thou readest.

186
00:12:02,599 --> 00:12:04,040
He was searching.

187
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:06,120
He was in Jerusalem to worship.

188
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,800
He was reading the scriptures

189
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,199
but I want you to understand not only was he searching

190
00:12:11,199 --> 00:12:13,160
but we see that he was submissive.

191
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:15,960
We see it in his response in verse 31.

192
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,639
It's a submissive response.

193
00:12:17,639 --> 00:12:19,399
It's a response of humility when he says,

194
00:12:19,399 --> 00:12:24,399
how can I except some man should guide me?

195
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:27,220
You know, we live in a world that's full of pride.

196
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,559
Arrogance.

197
00:12:29,559 --> 00:12:30,720
I don't need your help.

198
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,240
I'll figure it out myself.

199
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:36,479
People going to the wrong places to try to find answers

200
00:12:36,479 --> 00:12:40,039
but we find that this man demonstrated a heart of humility,

201
00:12:40,039 --> 00:12:43,720
a spirit of submission when he says to Philip,

202
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,720
now think about this.

203
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,639
Many of us are familiar with the text of scripture

204
00:12:46,679 --> 00:12:48,600
but I want you to put yourself there

205
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,000
just for a moment this morning

206
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,320
and I want you to think about Philip

207
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,399
and he's ministering and he's preaching in Samaria

208
00:12:53,399 --> 00:12:56,360
and God calls him and he goes and he's there on this road

209
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:59,440
and he sees in the spirit of God says, go into his chariot.

210
00:13:01,839 --> 00:13:03,119
The eunuch as best we know,

211
00:13:03,119 --> 00:13:05,800
the eunuch and Philip had never met each other before.

212
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,960
And God through the spirit says, get into his chariot.

213
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,960
Now what would you think if someone climbed in your chariot?

214
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:22,119
And he says, understand this now what thou readest.

215
00:13:23,199 --> 00:13:24,600
How can I?

216
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,440
How can I?

217
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:29,919
It's amazing the spiritual level that's taking place here

218
00:13:29,919 --> 00:13:33,279
in Acts chapter eight and this scene, it's amazing.

219
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:34,399
Yes, he's confused.

220
00:13:34,399 --> 00:13:36,559
He'd been searching, he's submissive.

221
00:13:36,559 --> 00:13:38,039
He wants an answer.

222
00:13:38,039 --> 00:13:40,039
He's desiring to know truth.

223
00:13:40,039 --> 00:13:42,520
I believe this morning that if you truly want to know

224
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:44,960
the truth, that the one who is the truth

225
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,800
will make it known to you.

226
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,679
He says, I am the way, the truth and the life.

227
00:13:48,679 --> 00:13:51,119
No man cometh unto the father but by me.

228
00:13:51,119 --> 00:13:53,800
And if you truly want to know truth,

229
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:55,880
he will reveal himself to you.

230
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:57,960
Pilate stood before the Lord Jesus Christ

231
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,479
before he went to that cross and he said, what is truth?

232
00:14:00,479 --> 00:14:03,000
Unfortunately, he did not stand around long enough

233
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,440
to get an answer and truth stood right before him.

234
00:14:07,759 --> 00:14:09,559
Sanctify them through thy word.

235
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,600
Thy word is truth.

236
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,559
I'm thankful that there's truth.

237
00:14:15,559 --> 00:14:17,519
