00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:39,440
but we have the clarity of the gospel.

721
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:40,880
The gospel's powerful.

722
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:43,000
It's been entrusted to us,

723
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:45,760
and we can go forth and preach the gospel to every creature,

724
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:48,720
and we can see people born again, converted,

725
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:50,120
saved by the blood of Christ.

726
00:40:50,120 --> 00:40:52,600
I can't save anyone, you can't save anyone,

727
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:56,680
but I'm so thankful to know the Savior of the world, amen?

728
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:58,020
The Bible tells us this.

729
00:40:58,020 --> 00:40:59,660
I'll read just a couple of verses of Scripture

730
00:40:59,660 --> 00:41:01,140
in 1 Timothy chapter number one,

731
00:41:01,140 --> 00:41:03,020
and we'll be done here in just a moment,

732
00:41:03,020 --> 00:41:04,860
but in 1 Timothy chapter number one,

733
00:41:04,860 --> 00:41:07,740
in verses 12 through 15, the Bible tells us

734
00:41:07,740 --> 00:41:10,620
as Paul is giving his own personal testimony,

735
00:41:10,620 --> 00:41:12,260
he says this in verse number 12,

736
00:41:12,260 --> 00:41:14,660
and I thank Christ Jesus, our Lord,

737
00:41:14,660 --> 00:41:17,280
who hath enabled me, for that he counted me faithful,

738
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:18,860
putting me in the ministry,

739
00:41:18,860 --> 00:41:23,760
who was before a blasphemer and a persecutor and injurious,

740
00:41:23,760 --> 00:41:26,660
but I obtained mercy.

741
00:41:26,700 --> 00:41:28,940
Our God is rich in mercy,

742
00:41:28,940 --> 00:41:31,420
because I did it ignorantly in unbelief,

743
00:41:31,420 --> 00:41:35,220
and the grace of our Lord was exceeding abundant

744
00:41:35,220 --> 00:41:37,940
with faith and love, which is in Christ Jesus.

745
00:41:37,940 --> 00:41:42,380
This is a faithful saying and worthy of all acceptation,

746
00:41:42,380 --> 00:41:46,380
that Christ Jesus came into the world to do what?

747
00:41:46,380 --> 00:41:49,880
To save sinners, of whom I am chief.

748
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:51,980
Listen, I'm so thankful that Jesus came into the world

749
00:41:51,980 --> 00:41:53,520
to save sinners.

750
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:54,820
Oh, did he leave us an example

751
00:41:54,820 --> 00:41:55,940
that we should follow his steps?

752
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:58,180
Absolutely, we read that in 1 Peter.

753
00:41:58,180 --> 00:42:01,140
But his number one purpose for coming to this earth,

754
00:42:01,140 --> 00:42:05,460
he was born to die, to pay for the sin of humanity,

755
00:42:05,460 --> 00:42:07,600
to save sinners.

756
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:11,380
And we find that Paul is confessing here,

757
00:42:11,380 --> 00:42:13,900
and he's proclaiming the truth of the purpose

758
00:42:13,900 --> 00:42:16,900
of Christ's birth and his life and his death

759
00:42:16,900 --> 00:42:20,420
and the reality that all men need to be saved.

760
00:42:21,580 --> 00:42:24,280
In Hebrews chapter seven, the Bible tells us this

761
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:26,840
in verse number 25, a verse of scripture

762
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:30,360
that brings great comfort and encouragement to us.

763
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:31,880
Wherefore, speaking of the Lord,

764
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:34,160
he is able also to save them to the uttermost

765
00:42:34,160 --> 00:42:35,740
that come unto God by him,

766
00:42:35,740 --> 00:42:38,700
seeing he ever liveth to make intercession for them.

767
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:43,280
2 Peter in chapter three and verse nine,

768
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:45,420
the Lord is not slack concerning his promises.

769
00:42:45,420 --> 00:42:47,480
Some men count slackness.

770
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:48,640
But as longsuffering to us,

771
00:42:48,640 --> 00:42:51,200
we're not willing that any should perish,

772
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:53,640
but that all should come to repentance.

773
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:54,480
Can I tell you this morning,

774
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:56,180
the Lake of Fire is a real place.

775
00:42:58,240 --> 00:43:00,160
Hell is forever.

776
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:02,400
The Lake of Fire, it's forever.

777
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:03,540
It's a real place.

778
00:43:04,440 --> 00:43:07,260
The Bible gives us, in the gospel of Luke,

779
00:43:08,280 --> 00:43:13,120
interaction between a rich man, Lazarus, Abraham.

780
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:17,140
That rich man is in torments in hell.

781
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:21,240
And when he could find no relief for himself,

782
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:23,720
his one request was simply this,

783
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:27,120
let him go to my brother's house, my father's house,

784
00:43:27,120 --> 00:43:29,160
because I have five brethren,

785
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:31,440
and I don't want him to come here.

786
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:33,280
He knew it was a place of torment.

787
00:43:33,280 --> 00:43:37,460
There's a cry from hell from that man.

788
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:41,400
The Bible tells us that God is not willing

789
00:43:41,400 --> 00:43:42,320
that any should perish,

790
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:44,360
but that all should come to repentance.

791
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:46,360
The choice is yours.

792
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:48,000
The Bible says, for whosoever shall call

793
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:50,040
upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.

794
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:53,240
In John chapter six and verse 37,

795
00:43:53,240 --> 00:43:55,040
the latter part of the verse says this,

796
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:59,180
he that cometh to me, I will in no wise cast out.

797
00:44:00,120 --> 00:44:01,900
He's a loving Savior.

798
00:44:01,900 --> 00:44:03,800
He wants to be your Savior.

799
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:05,360
I'm thankful that I can stand here today

800
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:06,680
and say he's my Savior.

801
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:08,560
I'm thankful that I can read Acts chapter number eight

802
00:44:08,560 --> 00:44:12,160
and say he's Philip's Savior, and he's the eunuch's Savior.

803
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:15,920
But the real question this morning is, is he your Savior?

804
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:18,279
Have you trusted Jesus Christ as your personal Savior?

805
00:44:18,279 --> 00:44:20,940
Do you know for sure, without any doubt,

806
00:44:21,640 --> 00:44:22,460
that heaven is your home?

807
00:44:22,460 --> 00:44:23,300
God loves you.

808
00:44:24,179 --> 00:44:27,860
He wants you to know that you have eternal life.

809
00:44:27,860 --> 00:44:30,740
He wants you to know that heaven is your home.

810
00:44:30,740 --> 00:44:33,380
There's confusion, there's clarity,

811
00:44:33,380 --> 00:44:34,300
and there's a conversion.

812
00:44:34,300 --> 00:44:35,140
Let's pray.

813
00:44:35,140 --> 00:44:36,100
Father, we love you.

814
00:44:36,100 --> 00:44:37,300
We thank you for loving us.

815
00:44:37,300 --> 00:44:39,580
We thank you for your word.

816
00:44:39,580 --> 00:44:40,779
I pray that in this moment,

817
00:44:40,779 --> 00:44:45,779
the Holy Spirit would do a work that only he could do.

818
00:44:47,179 --> 00:44:49,339
If there's one here, maybe there's several here

819
00:44:49,339 --> 00:44:50,500
that are not saved,

820
00:44:51,380 --> 00:44:54,860
God, would you draw them to yourself in this moment?

821
00:44:55,980 --> 00:44:57,540
We're gonna have an invitation.

822
00:44:59,899 --> 00:45:01,020
If you're saved this morning,

823
00:45:01,020 --> 00:45:02,460
maybe you need to come and ask God

824
00:45:02,460 --> 00:45:05,100
to give you those divine opportunities,

825
00:45:05,100 --> 00:45:07,899
that you'd be prepared like Philip was,

826
00:45:07,899 --> 00:45:09,500
that you'd be engaged in proclaiming

827
00:45:09,500 --> 00:45:11,700
the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.

828
00:45:13,540 --> 00:45:15,940
But maybe this morning you're here and you're lost.

829
00:45:15,940 --> 00:45:17,380
You've never been born again.

830
00:45:18,380 --> 00:45:19,820
We'd love to take a Bible and show you

831
00:45:19,820 --> 00:45:22,380
how you can know for sure that heaven is your home.

832
00:45:23,740 --> 00:45:24,820
If you're a man, you come,

833
00:45:24,820 --> 00:45:27,179
and Brother Mark will speak with you.

834
00:45:27,179 --> 00:45:30,820
Your lady, Holly, will speak with you.

835
00:45:30,820 --> 00:45:32,260
We'd never embarrass you,

836
00:45:33,140 --> 00:45:34,179
but we don't want you to leave here

837
00:45:34,179 --> 00:45:36,619
without knowing for sure that heaven's your home.

838
00:45:37,940 --> 00:45:41,619
God, I pray that you do a work that you'd be glorified.

839
00:45:41,619 --> 00:45:42,740
Have your will and have your way,

840
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:44,380
and we'll thank you for it in Christ's name.

841
00:45:44,380 --> 00:45:46,179
We pray, would you stand with me?

842
00:45:46,820 --> 00:45:47,980
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed.

843
00:45:47,980 --> 00:45:50,300
Kimberly's gonna play quietly on the piano,

844
00:45:50,300 --> 00:45:52,020
and as she does, the altar's open.

845
00:45:52,020 --> 00:45:54,820
If you're not sure of heaven, would you come?

846
00:45:54,820 --> 00:45:55,660
Would you come?

847
00:45:55,660 --> 00:45:56,500
Don't delay.

848
00:45:58,660 --> 00:45:59,500
What is your life?

849
00:45:59,500 --> 00:46:00,339
It's a vapor.

